  "body": "I'm trying to connect to the ethereum node through node js. I'm using a Docker network. The command which I used is this:\r\n\r\n> this connection geth command:\r\n- [ ] geth --testnet  --datadir /testchain/geth/chaindata  --cache 8196 --rpcport 3000 --rpcaddr 192.168.3.2 --rpccorsdomain \"*\" --rpcapi \"eth,net,personal,web3,db,txpool\" --port 35355\r\n\r\n> --rpcaddr 192.168.3.2 this my node.js api ip.they are all in the same docker network.\r\n\r\nI'm trying connect ethereum node  with this ip X.X.X.2:3000 \r\nMy ethereum node's ip is X.X.X.3:8545\r\n\r\nWhy am I getting this error: \r\nError: Connection refused or URL couldn't be resolved: http://X.X.X.2:3000\r\n",
